  "architecture_summary": "Unicoder-VL is a universal encoder based on a multi-layer Transformer that jointly encodes visual regions and textual tokens for cross-modal pre-training. It uses three pre-training tasks—Masked Language Modeling (MLM), Masked Object Classification (MOC) and Visual-linguistic Matching (VLM)—and transfers to downstream vision-language tasks with a simple additional output layer.",
